{"word":"εὔθυνα","slug":"εὔθυνα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n44065\" key=\"eu)/quna\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">εὔθῡνα</orth> (v. infr.), <gen lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gen\">ἡ</gen>, gen. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">εὐθύνης</foreign>, acc. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">εὔθυναν</foreign>, nom. pl. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">εὔθυναι</foreign>: (<etym lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"etym\">εὐθύνω</etym>): —<sense id=\"n44065.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">setting straight, correction, chastisement</tr_>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0059.tlg022:326e\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Pl.\">Pl.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Prt.\">Prt.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">326e</biblScope> </bibl> (pl.); <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">calling to account,</tr_> <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ POxy.\">POxy.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1203.9</biblScope> </bibl> <date TEIform=\"date\">(i A.D.)</date>, etc. </sense> <sense n=\"II\" id=\"n44065.1\" level=\"2\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> esp. at Athens, <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">public examination of the conduct of officials</tr_>, held on the expiration of their term of office (dist. fr. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">λόγος</foreign> 'rendering of accounts', <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">οὔτε χρήματα διαχειρίσας τῆς πόλεως δίδωμι λόγον αὐτῶν, οὔτε ἀρχὴν ἄρξας οὐδεμίαν εὐθύνας ὑπέχω αὐτῆς</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0540.tlg024.perseus-grc1:26\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Lys.\">Lys.</